Add automated backup system with scheduled exports, rotation, and cloud storage integration.

## Current Backup System
Manual export via /backup page - requires user action.

## Automated Backup Requirements
1. **Scheduled backups** - Daily, weekly, monthly
2. **Automatic rotation** - Keep last N backups
3. **Cloud storage** - S3/R2/B2 integration
4. **Backup verification** - Test restore process
5. **Notifications** - Alert on success/failure
6. **Retention policies** - Delete old backups
7. **Incremental backups** - Only changed data

## Architecture

### Backup Scheduler (Cron Jobs)
Use node-cron for scheduling:
```typescript
// apps/web/server/jobs/backup-scheduler.ts
import cron from "node-cron";
import { performBackup } from "./backup-job";

// Daily backup at 2 AM
cron.schedule("0 2 * * *", async () => {
  await performBackup("daily");
});

// Weekly backup on Sunday at 3 AM
cron.schedule("0 3 * * 0", async () => {
  await performBackup("weekly");
});

// Monthly backup on 1st at 4 AM
cron.schedule("0 4 1 * *", async () => {
  await performBackup("monthly");
});
```

### Backup Job Implementation
```typescript
// apps/web/server/jobs/backup-job.ts
import { exportFamilyData } from "@vamsa/lib/backup";
import { uploadToS3 } from "../lib/storage";
import { notifyBackupComplete } from "../server/notifications";

export async function performBackup(type: "daily" | "weekly" | "monthly") {
  const startTime = Date.now();
  logger.info({ type }, "Starting automated backup");

  try {
    // Export data
    const backup = await exportFamilyData({
      includePeople: true,
      includeRelationships: true,
      includeEvents: true,
      includePlaces: true,
      includeMedia: true,
      includeAuditLogs: type === "monthly", // Full audit only monthly
      includeSettings: true
    });

    // Generate filename with timestamp
    const timestamp = new Date().toISOString().replace(/[:.]/g, "-");
    const filename = `vamsa-backup-${type}-${timestamp}.zip`;

    // Save locally first
    const localPath = `./backups/${filename}`;
    await fs.writeFile(localPath, backup.buffer);

    // Upload to cloud storage
    if (process.env.BACKUP_STORAGE === "s3") {
      await uploadToS3(filename, backup.buffer);
    }

    // Record backup in database
    await prisma.backup.create({
      data: {
        filename,
        type,
        size: backup.size,
        location: process.env.BACKUP_STORAGE || "local",
        status: "COMPLETED",
        duration: Date.now() - startTime
      }
    });

    // Clean up old backups
    await rotateBackups(type);

    // Notify admins
    await notifyBackupComplete(filename, backup.size);

    logger.info({ filename, duration: Date.now() - startTime }, "Backup completed");

  } catch (error) {
    logger.error({ error, type }, "Backup failed");

    // Record failure
    await prisma.backup.create({
      data: {
        filename: `failed-${type}-${Date.now()}`,
        type,
        status: "FAILED",
        error: error.message
      }
    });

    // Alert admins
    await notifyBackupFailed(type, error.message);

    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Database Schema

### Backup Model
```prisma
model Backup {
  id String @id @default(cuid())
  filename String
  type String  // "daily", "weekly", "monthly", "manual"
  size BigInt
  location String  // "local", "s3", "r2", "b2"
  status String  // "PENDING", "COMPLETED", "FAILED"
  error String?
  duration Int?  // milliseconds

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  deletedAt DateTime?  // Soft delete for retention

  @@index([type, createdAt])
  @@index([status])
}

model BackupSettings {
  id String @id @default(cuid())

  // Schedule
  dailyEnabled Boolean @default(true)
  dailyTime String @default("02:00")  // HH:MM format
  weeklyEnabled Boolean @default(true)
  weeklyDay Int @default(0)  // 0 = Sunday
  weeklyTime String @default("03:00")
  monthlyEnabled Boolean @default(true)
  monthlyDay Int @default(1)  // 1st of month
  monthlyTime String @default("04:00")

  // Retention
  dailyRetention Int @default(7)  // Keep 7 daily backups
  weeklyRetention Int @default(4)  // Keep 4 weekly backups
  monthlyRetention Int @default(12)  // Keep 12 monthly backups

  // Storage
  storageProvider String @default("local")  // "local", "s3", "r2", "b2"
  storageBucket String?
  storageRegion String?

  // Notifications
  notifyOnSuccess Boolean @default(false)
  notifyOnFailure Boolean @default(true)
  notificationEmails String[]  // JSON array

  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
}
```

## Backup Rotation Strategy
```typescript
async function rotateBackups(type: "daily" | "weekly" | "monthly") {
  const settings = await prisma.backupSettings.findFirst();

  const retentionMap = {
    daily: settings.dailyRetention,
    weekly: settings.weeklyRetention,
    monthly: settings.monthlyRetention
  };

  const keepCount = retentionMap[type];

  // Get all backups of this type, oldest first
  const backups = await prisma.backup.findMany({
    where: { type, status: "COMPLETED", deletedAt: null },
    orderBy: { createdAt: "desc" },
    skip: keepCount  // Skip the ones we want to keep
  });

  // Delete old backups
  for (const backup of backups) {
    logger.info({ filename: backup.filename }, "Deleting old backup");

    // Delete from cloud storage
    if (backup.location === "s3") {
      await deleteFromS3(backup.filename);
    }

    // Delete from local storage
    const localPath = `./backups/${backup.filename}`;
    if (await fs.exists(localPath)) {
      await fs.unlink(localPath);
    }

    // Soft delete in database
    await prisma.backup.update({
      where: { id: backup.id },
      data: { deletedAt: new Date() }
    });
  }
}
```

