Allow users who sign in via OIDC to claim their existing person profiles in the family tree.

## Context
After implementing OIDC authentication, users need a way to link their SSO account to their person record in the family tree.

## Current Profile Claiming
Existing claimProfile flow requires:
- Email
- Person selection
- Password creation

## OIDC Profile Claiming Flow

### Scenario 1: First-time OIDC User
```
1. User signs in with Google (john@gmail.com)
2. System creates User account
3. System shows: "Welcome! Are you in this family tree?"
4. User searches and selects their person profile
5. System links User.personId to Person.id
6. User promoted to MEMBER role
```

### Scenario 2: Existing User Adding OIDC
```
1. User has password-based account
2. User clicks "Link Google Account" in settings
3. OAuth flow completes
4. System links oidcProvider and oidcSubject to existing user
5. User can now login with either password or Google
```

### Scenario 3: OIDC User Claiming Later
```
1. User signs in with Google
2. User skips profile claiming initially
3. User browses as VIEWER
4. Later, user goes to Profile Settings
5. User claims their person profile
6. Auto-promoted to MEMBER
```

## Database Schema Updates
```prisma
model User {
  // ... existing fields

  profileClaimStatus String @default("PENDING")  // PENDING, CLAIMED, SKIPPED
  profileClaimedAt DateTime?

  // OIDC fields (already added in previous bead)
  oidcProvider String?
  oidcSubject String?
}
```

## Server Functions

### Get Claimable Profiles (OIDC version)
```typescript
export const getOIDCClaimableProfiles = createServerFn({ method: "GET" })
  .handler(async () => {
    const user = await requireAuth();

    if (!user.oidcProvider) {
      throw new Error("Not an OIDC user");
    }

    // Get unclaimed living persons
    const claimedPersonIds = await prisma.user.findMany({
      where: { personId: { not: null } },
      select: { personId: true }
    }).then(users => users.map(u => u.personId).filter(Boolean));

    const profiles = await prisma.person.findMany({
      where: {
        isLiving: true,
        id: { notIn: claimedPersonIds }
      },
      select: {
        id: true,
        firstName: true,
        lastName: true,
        email: true,
        dateOfBirth: true
      },
      orderBy: [{ lastName: "asc" }, { firstName: "asc" }]
    });

    // Suggest matches based on email or name
    const emailMatch = user.oidcEmail 
      ? profiles.filter(p => p.email === user.oidcEmail)
      : [];

    const nameMatch = profiles.filter(p => {
      const userName = user.name?.toLowerCase() || "";
      const personName = `${p.firstName} ${p.lastName}`.toLowerCase();
      return userName.includes(personName) || personName.includes(userName);
    });

    return {
      all: profiles,
      suggested: [...emailMatch, ...nameMatch].filter((v, i, a) => 
        a.findIndex(t => t.id === v.id) === i  // unique
      )
    };
  });
```

### Claim Profile (OIDC version)
```typescript
const oidcClaimProfileSchema = z.object({
  personId: z.string().min(1, "Please select your profile")
});

export const claimProfileOIDC = createServerFn({ method: "POST" })
  .inputValidator((data) => oidcClaimProfileSchema.parse(data))
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    const user = await requireAuth();
    const { personId } = data;

    // Verify user is OIDC user
    if (!user.oidcProvider) {
      throw new Error("This endpoint is for OIDC users only");
    }

    // Verify person exists and is living
    const person = await prisma.person.findUnique({
      where: { id: personId }
    });

    if (!person) {
      throw new Error("Profile not found");
    }

    if (!person.isLiving) {
      throw new Error("Cannot claim a non-living profile");
    }

    // Verify no other user has claimed this person
    const existingClaim = await prisma.user.findUnique({
      where: { personId }
    });

    if (existingClaim) {
      throw new Error("This profile is already claimed");
    }

    // Link user to person and promote to MEMBER
    await prisma.user.update({
      where: { id: user.id },
      data: {
        personId,
        role: "MEMBER",
        profileClaimStatus: "CLAIMED",
        profileClaimedAt: new Date()
      }
    });

    // Send notification to admins
    await notifyNewMemberJoined(user.id);

    return { success: true };
  });
```

